main event: A round and flat object was reported sighted in Sacramento, California on April 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object had a textured, rough surface with diagonal streaks of light and a dark spot in the center., It emitted a whitish-red trail when it disappeared., The sighting lasted for approximately 25 to 30 minutes., The observer used a 10 power telescope and Army type binoculars to observe the object., The investigation suggested that Venus could have been mistaken for the UFO.
witness description: Mrs. Jean W. May, a civilian housewife from Rancho Cordova.
